cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the relationship between altmetrics and the scientific quality of papers, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of altmetrics and peer assessments is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of dimensions of measurement for traditional metrics and altmetrics is related to social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the regression analysis of the relationship between metrics and quality of papers is related to software engineering (cs.SD).
